We observe that increasing {{arxiv_2405_02732_FO0077||FO}} is very useful, but has diminishing returns beyond a certain value. Note that larger {{arxiv_2405_02732_FO0078||FO}} also increase the cost for invoking the LLM more often.
For small {{arxiv_2405_02732_FO0079||FO}}, there is no benefit from larger batches, but this
changes for large {{arxiv_2405_02732_FO0080||FO}}, where bigger batches keep improving recall.
Note that this also increases LLM costs, as we pass more tokens into
the inference.